"Here's your requested Python coding question:\n\n```\n{\n    \"title\": \"Hard: Longest Increasing Subsequence\",\n    \"description\": \"Given an integer array, find the longest increasing subsequence.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef longest_increasing_subsequence(nums: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the length of the longest increasing subsequence in the input list.\\n\",\n    \"code\": \"\"\"\nimport bisect\n\ndef longest_increasing_subsequence(nums: list[int]) -> int:\n    if not nums:\n        return 0\n    \n    dp = [nums[0]]\n    \n    for num in nums[1:]:\n        if num > dp[-1]:\n            dp.append(num)\n        else:\n            idx = bisect.bisect_left(dp, num)\n            dp[idx] = num\n    \n    return len(dp)\n    \"\"\",\n    \"tests\": [\n        \"assert longest_increasing_subsequence([1, 2, 3, 4]) == 4\",\n        \"assert longest_increasing_subsequence([1, 3, 6, 7]) == 4\",\n        \"assert longest_increasing_subsequence([1, 2, 5, 6, 8]) == 5\",\n        \"assert longest_increasing_subsequence([]) == 0\"\n    ]\n}\n```\nI hope you enjoy this problem!"